reviews.review: J.J. Abrams said an awesome job finishing the Skywalker saga.
Don't believe any nonsense about the movie! It's an excellent movie and brings the whole series to a close. Must see.

Decent movie, but nothing new, nothing epic, somewhat predictable, and apologized for The Last Jedi, in the first few minutes. No creative way to end the saga other than following the typical formula - which was still better than The Last Jedi, you could literally watch The Force Awakens then The Rise of Skywalker, and you would miss nothing.
The best movie ever! How they ended it was phenomenal!! :)

I thought it gave the Skywalkers a good, decent ending, I felt unsatisfied with TLJ but TROS gave me some closure. I’ll admit that I cried a lot, the film had really great moments and some moments I felt could had more weight. Be ready because it was a little fast paced, there were a lot of scenes that happened too quickly imo that I felt could have been savored if it were slowed down. The final confrontation again happened a little too fast but overall I felt good.

I was so glad with how they fixed the problems created by The Last Jedi. The finale of the sequel trilogy redeems the two garbage films that came before it, just as Revenge of The Sith did to the prequel trilogy.

Great movie!!! Not epic but great. Fixed the mess up of the last Jedi. Very longtime fan of the Star Wars for 30+ years. Only drawback is they spent a lot of time fixing the last Jedi that it seems like it was rushed. No dead time action front to back. Sidious was a great piece. Force heal and Drain like the video games mass powers were used. Sorry trying not to spoil. Great movie would have been a great trilogy if number 2 was in line with this.
I thought the movie was great, there did appear to be some loose ends that needed to be addressed. this movie did that. nothing let me down about this movie. I wanted more Snoke.
Awsom fast fun exciting answers questions and had an ending that I liked. It is just what was needed after the Last Jedi put so much in limbo. It makes all 9 movies work together.
Saw it twice in a row and was equally enthralled both times! Sure there are a few elements that I didn’t care for, but overall it is a great homage to the Skywalker saga.
